Established: June 12, 1944
Named for the prominent bend in the Rio Grande along the U.S.â€“Mexico border, this park encompasses a large and remote part of the Chihuahuan Desert. Its main attraction is backcountry recreation in the arid Chisos Mountains and in canyons along the river. A wide variety of Cretaceous And Tertiary fossils as well as cultural artifacts of Native Americans also exist within its borders.